import { Button, Form } from "react-bootstrap";


function FormInput({AddObject}) {
    const style = {
        border: "1px solid black",
        padding: "15px",
        margin: "20px",
        width: "400px"
    }


    return <Form style={style}>
        <Form.Group className="mb-3" controlId="exampleForm.ControlInput1">
            <Form.Label>Name</Form.Label>
            <Form.Control type="text" ref={refName} placeholder="Email" />
        </Form.Group>
        <Form.Group className="mb-3" >
            <Form.Label>Profile</Form.Label>
            <Form.Control type="text" ref={refProfile} placeholder="Profile" />
        </Form.Group>
        <Form.Group className="mb-3" controlId="exampleForm.ControlInput1">
            <Form.Label>Phone</Form.Label>
            <Form.Control type="number" ref={refNumber} placeholder="number" />
        </Form.Group>
        <Button type="button" variant="success" onClick={AddObject}>Add Data</Button>
    </Form>
}
export default FormInput
